1
00:00:09,960 --> 00:00:10,960
Fukami.

2
00:00:12,340 --> 00:00:15,840
Can we just stay friends forever?

3
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:20,520
Being around you

4
00:00:21,260 --> 00:00:23,340
when you're just being yourself...

5
00:00:25,820 --> 00:00:27,610
it's the only time

6
00:00:27,650 --> 00:00:29,420
I feel like I can really breathe.

7
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:33,400
We can just meet up
and hook up occasionally.

8
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:36,220
I don't mind if you're seeing someone else.

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:40,050
And if that makes things too messy,

10
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:41,860
we don't even have to sleep together.

11
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:45,900
So please, just stay in my life...

12
00:00:52,540 --> 00:00:56,540
Actually, let's not be friends.

13
00:01:04,960 --> 00:01:07,160
Sorry, I'm being a pain, aren't I?

14
00:01:16,460 --> 00:01:19,380
This really is the last time I'll ask.

15
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:27,780
"Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami"
(Final Episode)

16
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,640
Let's stop being just friends.

17
00:01:35,980 --> 00:01:37,500
Let's be a couple.

18
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:40,760
The two of us.

19
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:48,160
Wait, what?

20
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,850
Where is this coming from?

21
00:01:52,643 --> 00:01:56,633
I've always been terrified
of being tied down,

22
00:01:58,033 --> 00:02:03,033
and the weight of being
responsible for someone.

23
00:02:05,620 --> 00:02:07,700
I never thought I was capable of it.

24
00:02:13,540 --> 00:02:15,880
But if it's what you want, I'm in.

25
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:22,080
If you want us to be together,
then let's be together.

26
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:31,300
Don't say something so heartbreaking.

27
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,580
It's okay, really.

28
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:38,809
I get it. You just think my body is great,

29
00:02:38,810 --> 00:02:40,880
and that's why you can't let go.

30
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:45,809
You don't have to force yourself for me.

31
00:02:45,810 --> 00:02:47,680
About us being a couple...

32
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,669
As long as you can just be yourself,

33
00:02:53,670 --> 00:02:56,000
that's all I really need.

34
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:59,900
I want you to eat well,

35
00:03:00,660 --> 00:03:02,120
and sleep soundly.

36
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:07,380
As long as you're happy, I'm happy.

37
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:14,120
Wow, I can't believe I just
said something so cheesy.

38
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:16,020
This is embarrassing.

39
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:17,760
Sorry, sorry.

40
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:19,880
I'm so sorry.

41
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,120
You know...

42
00:03:27,220 --> 00:03:31,020
I thought I'd just drift
through life forever.

43
00:03:35,620 --> 00:03:37,140
But after my dad got sick,

44
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:40,320
I started helping out
with the family business.

45
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:44,320
Everyone thought it was so hard on me
and felt sorry for me, but...

46
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:49,620
I actually felt a little happy.

47
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:53,020
Because for once, I was needed.

48
00:03:54,940 --> 00:03:56,140
I'm pretty awful, right?

49
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,489
Feeling happy like that

50
00:03:58,490 --> 00:03:59,860
while my own family was suffering.

51
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:05,080
Once I realized that,
I started to really hate myself.

52
00:04:08,186 --> 00:04:10,126
Then my mom passed away, too.

53
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:14,560
I kept trying so hard to
hold everything together.

54
00:04:15,177 --> 00:04:18,176
But then my sister
decided to get remarried,

55
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,200
and she didn't need me to worry anymore.

56
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:27,020
It felt like I'd been left all alone
in the middle of nowhere.

57
00:04:29,780 --> 00:04:31,640
A little while after that,

58
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:34,580
was when we went on that business trip.

59
00:04:43,180 --> 00:04:44,520
Being with you...

60
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:48,420
made me realize, "Hey,
I can actually do this."

61
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:51,740
I was just so moved and surprised.

62
00:04:53,780 --> 00:04:56,660
I hadn't even processed
whether I liked you yet.

63
00:04:58,260 --> 00:04:59,940
It's different from how I value my family,

64
00:05:00,620 --> 00:05:02,400
or how much I like having sex.

65
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,340
It's just... different.

66
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:09,760
I kept wondering what makes
that one person so special...

67
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:18,610
So, did you ever find the answer?

68
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:23,080
I want you to be happy and keep smiling,

69
00:05:28,980 --> 00:05:29,830
so I thought to myself,

70
00:05:29,831 --> 00:05:32,060
maybe it's better if we
don't see each other.

71
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:37,060
But seeing you at the office was torture.

72
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:40,240
I just wanted to reach out and touch you.

73
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:47,280
And I couldn't stand the thought of you
finding happiness with someone else.

74
00:05:51,380 --> 00:05:52,820
Is "love"...

75
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,080
always this much of a mess?

76
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:00,360
I'm sorry if I've got it all wrong.

77
00:06:05,460 --> 00:06:07,550
You haven't.

78
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:11,100
Actually...

79
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,200
the whole time we were apart,

80
00:06:15,580 --> 00:06:16,900
I was feeling the exact same way.

81
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:20,100
What was I even so afraid of?

82
00:06:21,220 --> 00:06:23,159
The person standing in front of me

83
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:25,080
is just a human being, like me.

84
00:06:26,060 --> 00:06:29,060
With your own worries and doubts.

85
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,780
I might not be able to understand it all,

86
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:51,760
but I truly want to understand
everything you're going through.

87
00:06:53,260 --> 00:06:55,820
When things are hard, tell me sooner.

88
00:06:58,180 --> 00:07:02,140
We'll figure it out together.

89
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:34,460
I love you.

90
00:07:39,650 --> 00:07:41,110
You don't have to say anything back.

91
00:07:42,260 --> 00:07:44,080
I know you're not great at this stuff.

92
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:47,140
It's just...

93
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:52,120
I wanted you to let me say it.

94
00:07:59,340 --> 00:08:01,080
I don't think I can hold it in anymore.

95
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:32,160
You really are something else.

96
00:08:47,380 --> 00:08:49,920
Your hands are shaking.

97
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:55,640
I'm a little nervous, too.

98
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,220
I want to be gentle with you.

99
00:09:05,380 --> 00:09:09,180
I feel like I could be
infinitely gentle with you.

100
00:09:14,340 --> 00:09:15,400
How does that feel?

101
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:21,080
I'm so happy, I could die.

102
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,200
Yuu.

103
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:30,920
You...

104
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:36,340
So you actually knew my name.

105
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,560
Of course I did.

106
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:41,960
The names of the people I've slept with...

107
00:09:46,980 --> 00:09:48,820
I know them, too.

108
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,900
Your name, I mean.

109
00:09:54,420 --> 00:09:57,980
Then... go ahead and say it.

110
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,510
Akihiro.

111
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:13,560
I love you.

112
00:10:16,990 --> 00:10:18,260
I love you.

113
00:10:22,310 --> 00:10:26,270
Fukami, I love you.

114
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,000
When do you leave?

115
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,440
Next Monday.

116
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:43,840
That's so soon.

117
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:48,140
Let's see each other as
much as we can this week.

118
00:10:50,140 --> 00:10:51,620
Are you sure you're not overdoing it?

119
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,580
No, I'm fine.

120
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,660
I'm the one who wants to see you, anyway.

121
00:11:15,060 --> 00:11:16,060
Dammit...

122
00:11:16,273 --> 00:11:18,273
I guess we're doing the
long-distance thing, then.

123
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:20,460
Are you going to be lonely?

124
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:22,840
Yeah.

125
00:11:24,040 --> 00:11:27,060
Of course I don't want to be away from you.

126
00:11:29,766 --> 00:11:32,686
I've been thinking...

127
00:11:33,740 --> 00:11:35,800
No, don't do anything impulsive.

128
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:39,300
Let's just date for a while
before we decide anything.

129
00:11:40,340 --> 00:11:42,760
I can work remotely,

130
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:45,560
so it doesn't really matter where I live.

131
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:51,000
Can't I just come with you?

132
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:54,240
Should we move in together?

133
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:58,600
- If you don't want to, it's fine.
- I didn't say no.

134
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:01,140
I actually think it's a great idea.

135
00:12:01,180 --> 00:12:05,020
Starting our new life together in Hokkaido.

136
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:23,040
This guy is unbelievable...

137
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:28,360
"Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami"
